"Slag I missed again." Lunarpine watched her fly to tree number two, 
heard the hoot and saw her head in the direction of the third tree 
before seemingly vanishing in the thick branches and leaves. He moved 
right and cut through some thick bushes.
He opened his comm "What's the matter birdie you afraid to take me 
claw to claw, I'll even let you use your daggers if you want." 
Transforming back to wolf mode he stayed low. He could easily pick 
her off with a rifle blast, but that would defeat the purpose of the 
sparring.
(Much better Logo.)


--- In nbwrpg@egroups.com, logomorph@h... wrote:
> :Shadow Wing::
> 
> She stayed hovering up over the fallen tree.  She knew he could see 
> her now.  So she flew over to another tree and perched.  She hooted 
> at him. She figured she would be nice and let him know where she 
was.
> 
> She knew that she couldn't compete physically with him, so why not 
> have some fun before getting her tail feathers kicked.
> 
> She hooted a few more time and flew to another tree. She perched on 
a 
> high branch with thick foliage. Only this time,she held perfectly 
> still and didn't make a sound.
